Project Summary 7

In conclusion we created a full dashboard that had different reports that would help the dba in identifying processes that are working perfectly  and those that are hazardous giving them direction on where they can put their effort and priority. 

Attached is the Complete Pbix file for the entire project.  Click on the link attached . You Should have the following complete reports in the dashboard.


1. Dashboard Overview

This is the landing page of the report that shows the different processes on a high level. It has a time slicer for different time period and slicers for the different table types. It includes some visualizations such as a donut that shows the number of processes by the runtime sec group , a tree map for the number of processes by table types and KPIâ€™s at the bottom showing different measures such as total processes, number of processes that were successful, processes that failed ,processes that run perfectly within the set parameters and those that were hazardous ( FASTER THAN NORMAL OR SLOWER THAN NORMAL) . A navigation bar is provided on the top to navigate to different report pages.


2.  KPI REPORT

This report shows KPIâ€™s more detailed. It has a heat map that shows the number of processes during the week per hour with the heat map showing the total seconds run.The report has a clustered column that shows run time sec by the table name and table type. This report also  has a gauge that shows the completion percentage of the processes and other KPIâ€™s similar to the Overview dashboard.



3. PROCESSES PER HOUR

This report has a Matrix Table that Shows different processes run during every hour within the day and a clustered bar chart that shows  the number of processes by the run time group and table type.




4. Process Performance report

This report shows the number of processes that failed , completed successfully and those that were hazardous during every hour of the day. It also has some KPIâ€™s at the bottom and a slicer for the different performance criteria.
